waitForCompletion

public void waitForCompletion(long timeout)
                       throws MqttException
Description copied from interface: MqttDeliveryToken
Blocks the current thread until the message this is the token for completes delivery. This will only block for specified timeout period. If the delivery has not completed before the timeout occurs, this method will return - the MqttDeliveryToken.isComplete() method can be used to determine if the delivery is complete, or if the wait has timed out.

Specified by:
waitForCompletion in interface MqttDeliveryToken
Parameters:
timeout - the maximum amount of time to wait for, in milliseconds.
Throws:
MqttException - if there was a problem completing delivery of the message
